@node "introduction" "Introduction "

     @{b}Introduction @{ub}

The time blanker module shows a black screen with a digital clock. The clock
shows hours, minutes and seconds. After a configurable amount of time, the
clock jumps to a different randomly chosen position.
@endnode

@node "interface" "Interface "

     @{b}Interface @{ub}

The user interface contains two sliders at the top of the window. They are
used to set the @{i}update time @{ui}and the @{i}jump time.@{ui} The @{i}update time @{ui}is the time
that the blanker module waits before updating the clock. Normally, you should
set it to about one second (9 / 10 or 10 / 10 seconds). The @{i}jump time @{ui}is the
time that the blanker module waits before moving the clock to a newly chosen
random position.

Below these sliders you can find the @{i}screenmode @{ui}and the @{i}font @{ui}buttons. These
are used to set the @{i}screenmode @{ui}and the @{i}font @{ui}used for the clock respectively.
Their use is pretty self explanatory.

At the bottom of the screen are four additional buttons. With @{i}use @{ui}you can
change the settings temporarily (until you reboot) and with @{i}save @{ui}you can store
the settings on disk. @{i}Test @{ui}allows you to immediately see the effects of any
changes you just made. Finally, @{i}cancel @{ui}undoes all changes and reverts to the
previous used settings.
@endnode

